    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel, core and chop your<strong> apple[s]</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped apple </strong>to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>maple syrup </strong>and most of your <strong>ground cinnamon</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and your <strong>mixed berry compote</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>apple & berry compote filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/apple-and-berry-compote-pie-with-creme-fraiche-custard-and-candied-walnuts/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining ground cinnamon</strong> to a small bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>cinnamon sugar</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/apple-and-berry-compote-pie-with-creme-fraiche-custard-and-candied-walnuts/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Cut into 1 large rectangle per person and add to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Divide the <strong>apple & berry compote</strong> <strong>filling</strong> between one side of each pastry rectangle[s], leaving a 2cm border around the edge</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/apple-and-berry-compote-pie-with-creme-fraiche-custard-and-candied-walnuts/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Brush a little cold water around the edges of the pastry then carefully fold the pastry over and seal the edges firmly with your fingers</p><p>Crimp round all the edges with a fork to make a border</p><p>Sprinkle the pie[s] with the <strong>cinnamon sugar</strong> (reserve the bowl) \u2013 these are your <strong>apple & berry compote pie[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/apple-and-berry-compote-pie-with-creme-fraiche-custard-and-candied-walnuts/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the <strong>pie[s]</strong> in the oven for 15-20 min or until the pastry is golden and the filling is tender</p><p>Meanwhile, roughly chop your <strong>walnuts</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped walnuts</strong> to the reserved small bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>butter</strong> and the <strong>remaining maple syrup</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and put in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 1 min or until thickened and the nuts are coated, then leave to cool \u2013 these are your <strong>candied walnuts</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/apple-and-berry-compote-pie-with-creme-fraiche-custard-and-candied-walnuts/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Separate the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> from the whites by cracking your <strong>egg[s]</strong> over a bowl and catching the yolk in the shell</p><p>Transfer the <strong>yolk</strong> from one shell half to the other several times, until all the <strong>whites</strong> are in the bowl and you are left with the yolk in the shell (Tip: Hold onto those egg whites! They're perfect for meringues or a protein-rich omelette - they freeze well too)</p><p>Add your <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>cornflour</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and mix until completely combined</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/apple-and-berry-compote-pie-with-creme-fraiche-custard-and-candied-walnuts/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> to a pot with 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [170ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [170ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> and cook over a medium heat until the cream has melted and the mix is starting to simmer, then gradually pour the <strong>hot milk mix</strong> into the egg mix, whisking constantly as you pour it in, to stop lumps forming \u2013 this is your <strong>custard mix</strong></p><p>Wipe out the pot with kitchen paper, return the <strong>custard mix</strong> to the pan and cook over a low heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, until thickened but before any lumps form \u2013 this is your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche custard</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/apple-and-berry-compote-pie-with-creme-fraiche-custard-and-candied-walnuts/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Allow the pie[s] to cool for 5 min before serving</p><p>Serve the <strong>apple & berry compote pie[s]</strong> topped with the <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche custard </strong>and <strong>candied walnuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
